 AGRICULTURAL INFORMATION REVIEW COMMITTEE REPORT AND AFTERWARDS' A SUMMARY.     THE WORK OF THE AGRICULTURAL INFORMATION REVIEW COMMITTEE, SUPPORTED BY THEBRITISH LIBRARY RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT DEPARTMENT, IS DESCRIBED. THEFINDINGS OF THE COMMITTEE'S REPORT (BLRD REPORT 5469) IS OUTLINED. A SERIES OFONE-DAY SEMINARS HELD TO MAKE THE CONTENTS OF THE REPORT BETTER KNOWN TOINFLUENTIAL INDIVIDUALS WITHIN THE AGRICULTURAL INFORMATION SYSTEM, AND TOOBTAIN THEIR VIEWS ON THE FINDINGS OF THE REPORT ITSELF IS DESCRIBED. A FINALMEETING WAS HELD TO DISCUSS SOME OF THE PRIORITY ISSUES IDENTIFIED. THESEWERE: THE 'GREY' (NON-CONVENTIONAL) LITERATURE; REVIEW LITERATURE; DIRECTORYOF INFORMATION SOURCES; TRAINING AND EDUCATION IN INFORMATION HANDLING; USERNEEDS; CO-ORDINATION OF INFORMATION ACTIVITIES